The [[upper case]] form of the second [[letter]] of the modern [[w:Greek alphabet|Greek alphabet]], the [[lower case]] form is '''β'''; preceded by '''Α α''' and followed by '''Γ γ'''. It represents the [[w:Voiced labiodental fricative|voiced labiodental fricative]] sound of '''v''' found in the English words ''have'' and ''vase''.
